<subSubSection id="FEDAC3FD843332D3FD708799DCA820CC" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="comments">
<paragraph id="23B075730B5FC2322C57D09674E96D9B" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EC56CDFFE510FEEEBE360B70763119A8" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
<bibRefCitation id="EDF809F20387242F5B91E0BE6407919F" author="Briceno, B" editor="Morillo, GN" journalOrPublisher="2. Centro Editorial Litoramma C. A., Merida" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="599 - 711" refId="B2" refString="Briceno, B, 2010. Capitulo XXI Familia Poaceae (R.Br.) Barnhart (Gramineae). In: Morillo, GN, Briceno, B, Silva, JF, Eds., Botanica y Ecologia de las Monocotiledoneas de los Paramos en Venezuela, vol. 2. Centro Editorial Litoramma C. A., Merida: 599 - 711" title="Capitulo XXI Familia Poaceae (R. Br.) Barnhart (Gramineae)." volumeTitle="Botanica y Ecologia de las Monocotiledoneas de los Paramos en Venezuela, vol." year="2010">
<normalizedToken id="DDCDB81BDF153DFF40358031F2A3861F" originalValue="Briceño">Briceno</normalizedToken>
(2010)
</bibRefCitation>
proposed the new combination of 
<taxonomicName id="73498869E8D7AE866CAD717C3F896C5A" class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Calamagrostis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Calamagrostis meridensis" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="meridensis">
<emphasis id="494BCA35D56E63F325327F2DED7C7B64" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Calamagrostis meridensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for a taxon endemic to 
<normalizedToken id="1481F49D7130A02D1BBDE88BEDAC9E21" originalValue="páramos">paramos</normalizedToken>
of Venezuela. 
<bibRefCitation id="417FAF1303EC58D2DF5EFBFF95681505" author="Briceno, B" editor="Morillo, GN" journalOrPublisher="2. Centro Editorial Litoramma C. A., Merida" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="599 - 711" refId="B2" refString="Briceno, B, 2010. Capitulo XXI Familia Poaceae (R.Br.) Barnhart (Gramineae). In: Morillo, GN, Briceno, B, Silva, JF, Eds., Botanica y Ecologia de las Monocotiledoneas de los Paramos en Venezuela, vol. 2. Centro Editorial Litoramma C. A., Merida: 599 - 711" title="Capitulo XXI Familia Poaceae (R. Br.) Barnhart (Gramineae)." volumeTitle="Botanica y Ecologia de las Monocotiledoneas de los Paramos en Venezuela, vol." year="2010">
<normalizedToken id="17AE87030300B60693245F944D533397" originalValue="Briceño">Briceno</normalizedToken>
(2010)
</bibRefCitation>
transferred the species from 
<taxonomicName id="3B52FD4EAC66845E759111035CA6E6BD" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Agrostis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Agrostis" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="960DF65D0F018B1EE82DFC84A51DC5E9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Agrostis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="B551CC1F7BD63D5876692E7719E6841F" class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Calamagrostis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Calamagrostis" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="347F961CECAD8BAB630032A682E96A11" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Calamagrostis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the upper glume having 2-3 veins and anatomical characters such as all vascular bundles having a double sheath and without a notably angular shape and short cells over the veins can be solitary, in pairs or in short series. However, the species habit is noted as long rhizomatous to stoloniferous with geniculate culms, a habit unknown in 
<taxonomicName id="FCC923583EF7CFD4067EBBEA45E635C9" class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Calamagrostis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Calamagrostis" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7AE0904E84A328C828D6C564EDDDF0A7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Calamagrostis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="B9ECF747B3A975D8995750CDAD08212F" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Deschampsia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Deschampsia" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C6E48612F5522D231F1A324877D23F7C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Deschampsia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which are tufted or very-short rhizomatous and tussock-forming. This taxon is most likely a species of 
<taxonomicName id="71E4239681D62FB65522E17DF7D05E4C" authorityName="Scribner &amp; Merrill" authorityYear="1910" baseAuthorityName="Grisebach" class="Monocots" family="Poaceae" genus="Podagrostis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Podagrostis" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="939792C630F45938AF11E61DB867B3EB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Podagrostis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Griseb.) Scribn. &amp; Merr. based on the small spikelets (2.6-3.8 mm long), palea subequal to the lemma, awn often lacking, a rachilla extension that is usually absent or, when present, very short and glabrescent, a callus glabrous or rarely with scarce short hairs and short anthers 0.7-1 mm long. The number of veins of the upper glume has been considered as a distinguishing character to differentiate 
<taxonomicName id="116E487395A809D1969057AC52566CA4" authorityName="Scribner &amp; Merrill" authorityYear="1910" baseAuthorityName="Grisebach" class="Monocots" family="Poaceae" genus="Podagrostis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Podagrostis" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4D3D8F28E28873C14D9D660F658D90C6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Podagrostis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="CC7884BA1EC50F6C69AFA7D058C6F557" class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Calamagrostis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Calamagrostis" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="42CF8038221F27B0D747A64DC6F5524E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Calamagrostis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="D2B58D1FB4876A6E77C4E386C8D85A26" author="Rugolo de Agrasar, ZE" editor="Zuloaga, FO" journalOrPublisher="Poaceae: Pooideae Volumen 3 Tomo 2. IBODA-IMBIV, CONICET, Buenos Aires, Argentina" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="180 - 218" refId="B33" refString="Rugolo de Agrasar, ZE, 2012. Deyeuxia Clarion ex P. Beauv. In: Zuloaga, FO, Rugolo de Agrasar, ZE, Anton, AM, Eds., Flora Argentina. Poaceae: Pooideae Volumen 3 Tomo 2. IBODA-IMBIV, CONICET, Buenos Aires, Argentina: 180 - 218" title="Deyeuxia Clarion ex P. Beauv." volumeTitle="Flora Argentina." year="2012">
<normalizedToken id="F394A80D1FE124BD1E7B4D7227323BCE" originalValue="Rúgolo">Rugolo</normalizedToken>
de Agrasar 2012
</bibRefCitation>
) but the recent discovery of 
<taxonomicName id="1216760DD2A29E3AE20B235EA8E18661" authorityName="Sylvester &amp; Soreng" authorityYear="2019" class="Monocots" family="Poaceae" genus="Podagrostis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Podagrostis colombiana" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="colombiana">
<emphasis id="22459EE4191638E07A3FAD3D81C76CF1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Podagrostis colombiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Sylvester &amp; Soreng (
<bibRefCitation id="7920D84A46525B50C2104F771056CF7A" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s12225-019-9814-5" author="Sylvester, SP" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the United States National Herbarium" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" refId="B42" refString="Sylvester, SP, Soreng, RJ, Giraldo-Canas, D, in press. Podagrostiscolombiana sp. nov. (Poaceae): A new genus record and species for Colombia. Kew Bulletin. https://doi.org/10.1007/s12225-019-9814-5" title="Podagrostiscolombiana sp. nov. (Poaceae): A new genus record and species for Colombia. Kew Bulletin." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s12225-019-9814-5" year="in press">Sylvester et al. in press</bibRefCitation>
) from the Colombian Andes with well-developed lateral veins of the upper glume, large anthers and tussock-forming habit has shown these characters to be labile in 
<taxonomicName id="F52651D0ABA6780CEF9B7FD530734A8B" authorityName="Scribner &amp; Merrill" authorityYear="1910" baseAuthorityName="Grisebach" class="Monocots" family="Poaceae" genus="Podagrostis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Podagrostis" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="04210E2C83ABB121E37FFB3D4D54BBD1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Podagrostis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
